$t. 
|> 
<|| This video will show features associated with ||> 
<|| our XCSD image format and with a demo ||> 
<|| application that converts images into this ||>
<|| format and displays them (along with some ||>
<|| image-processing data) interactively. ||>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;
&#9135;&#9135;&#9135;&#9135;&#9135;&#9135;&#9135;&#9135;&#9135;&#9135;
<br>
<|| XCSD facilitates several forms of image ||>
<|| processing, such as one method (that will be ||>
<|| visualized in this video) involving calculations ||>
<|| of local color histograms. <| The goal here is ||>
<|| associating certain colors with thematic ||>
<|| roles within an image, such as foreground  ||>
<|| and background image areas. ||>
/.
$y.
($large-box)
 color:rgb(10,90,137);;font-weight:normal;
 background-color:rgba(245,245,210,220);
/.
$p# 3 5
/!
